IESO Selects International Business Machines Corp To Operate Ontario's Smart Meter Data Management And Repository System
Thursday, 7 Feb 2013 12:46am EST
International Business Machines Corp announced that it has been selected to continue supporting the Independent Electricity System Operator (IESO) to operate Ontario's Meter Data Management and Repository (MDM/R) system with new computing infrastructure and an updated operating environment. The five year CAD68.5 million contract was awarded following a competitive procurement process and includes options to extend to seven or 10 years. Under the agreement, IBM will enhance the overall performance of the MDM/R through new computing infrastructure, enhanced web services facility to support increasing volumes of requests for consumption information, enhanced disaster recovery capabilities, and operational improvements with a focus on reducing risk and costs.Â 
